external_knowledge:
- "Unseen" refers to TV series with a status of 'not seen' in the recommendations table;
- "Top 5" implies a limit of 5 results;
- "Highest ratings" means the average rating of the series in descending order;
- "Most recommendations" means the number of recommendations in descending order.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS num_series
FROM series
WHERE genre = 'Crime';

SELECT title, rating
FROM series
ORDER BY rating DESC;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT series_id) AS number_of_rated_series
FROM watch_history
WHERE rating IS NOT NULL;
